              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Player Comments</b> (total:41, showing:36-40) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=zone&tid=50')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:niteraven@eqmaps.com">NiteRaven</a> on Feb. 03, 2000 at 11:54am said...<br>
Can someone clarify the last few statements. You need a wizard to reach the plane of hate, but you have to cast the spell from Oasis? That doesn't make any sense. I have also heard of people dueling to get into the PoH... that one really confuses me.. hehe. One last question.. how do you exit the PoH besides gating out? and where does it take you?<br><br>
<a href="mailto:drc_alpha@yahoo.com">Razma Kindheart</a> of the Rallos Zek server on Feb. 01, 2000 at 05:17pm said...<br>
The entrence, correction, ZONE, which you need to be in to get to the PoH is the Oasis.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:cest1171@hotmail.com">Caranlron</a> of the Quellios server on Jan. 14, 2000 at 02:57pm said...<br>
There is no known way to get int PoH. You must use the wizard gating spell. This makes it much more dangerous than PoF because you can't run away<br><br>
<a href="mailto:erisun_t@yahoo.com">Erisun Taganro</a> of the Brell Serilis server on Dec. 07, 1999 at 11:41am said...<br>
You cannot bind in Plane of Hate. This is why its best to die and let cleric camp if things get sticky and not evacuate. Unless you got plenty of cash of course.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:karlchu@aol.com">Dubar</a> on Dec. 03, 1999 at 04:45pm said...<br>
Plane of hate is reached by a wizard spell which requires 200+pp gem. Its much better than Fear the fact that you're not attacked before you even finish zonign in. Be sure to bind right at the entrance so you dont have to pay another 200+pp to enter again<br><br>
